ruby-mechanize
------------------------------------------
The Mechanize library is used for automating interaction with websites. 
Mechanize automatically stores and sends cookies, follows redirects, can 
follow links, and submit forms. Form fields can be populated and 
submitted. Mechanize also keeps track of the sites that you have visited 
as a history.

Runtime requirements:
  ruby-1.8.6-1
  ruby-hpricot-0.6-1
  rubygems-0.9.4-1

Additional build requirements:
  cygport-0.3.8-1
  rake-0.7.2-1
  ruby-hoe-1.5.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://mechanize.rubyforge.org/mechanize/

Canonical download:
  http://rubyforge.org/projects/mechanize/files

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ruby-mechanize-0.7.5-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ruby-mechanize-0.7.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ruby-mechanize-0.7.5-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ruby-mechanize-0.7.5-X.tar.bz2

